SUPERIOR COURT OF CALIFORNIA, COUNTY OF LOS ANGELES
Civil Division
Northeast District, Alhambra Courthouse, Department V
24NNCV06082
JENNIFER BURBANK, et al. vs BRAD MARTINEZ, et al.
Judge: Honorable Sarah J. Heidel
Judicial Assistant: W. Delgado
Courtroom Assistant: K. Carrillo
APPEARANCES:
CSR: None
ERM: None
Deputy Sheriff: None
For Plaintiff(s): Joseph Wind Kellener via LA Court Connect
For Defendant(s): Shanna Marie Van Wagner via LA Court Connect
August 6, 2025
8:30 AM
NATURE OF PROCEEDINGS: Order to Show Cause Re: Dismissal Pursuant to C.C.P.
Sections 581(b)(4), 583.110 and 583.130 and/or Sanctions of up to $250.00 Pursuant to C.C.P.,
177.5; for Failure of Plaintiff to Attend 4/8/25 Order to Show Cause; Case Management
Conference
The above matters are called for hearing.
The Court reviews the court docket and notes three defendants have answered the complaint and
four defendants have been defaulted.
Court and counsel discuss the case.
The above Order to Show Cause is discharged.
The parties are ordered to telephonically meet and confer to prepare and file a Joint Status
Update five days prior to the next appearance. In addition to whatever issues the parties wish to
raise, the Court wants them to state what specific fact discovery still needs to be completed, and
include a timeline for depositions, and outline their plans for alternative dispute resolution.
Counsel are advised this Court aims to dispose of its cases within 18 months of filing and once it
sets the matter for trial, its trial dates are firm. Counsel are further advised that when this Court
does set trial dates, it can usually set them within 90 days of a trial setting conference should the
parties so desire.
Case Management Conference is continued to 12/02/2025 at 08:30 AM in Department V at
Alhambra Courthouse.
Notice is waived.
Minute Order
